==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Frighten
<hw>Fright"en</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp.</pos> <conjf>Frightened</conjf> <pr>(#)</pr>; <pos>p.
pr. & vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Frightening</conjf> <pr>(#)</pr>.]</vmorph>
<ety>[See <er>Fright</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety> <def>To disturb with
fear; to throw into a state of alarm or fright; to affright; to
terrify.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>More <qex>frightened</qex> than hurt.</q> <rj><qau>Old
Proverb.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Frightful</ent>⟦br⟧
